{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":8432,"record_hash":"sha256:7ad0d3c4a6a49bb732034d2eac591eaa0ba4872851bd2550697af011caf613aa","timestamp":"2026-05-07T20:08:45.594Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"::code-comment{title=\\\"[P2] Missing partial-write recovery coverage\\\" body=\\\"Tests cover missing transcript hash-set state when the transcript list still exists, but not the partial-write case where metadata hashes were recorded and transcript envelopes were not. A regression that derives transcript appends from metadata-new records would still pass.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs\\\" start=78 end=93 priority=2 confidence=0.78}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P2] Copied cwd redaction is untested\\\" body=\\\"Redaction integration tests cover copied session/message fields, but cwd is copied into the envelope without the same redaction path. Given the generic redaction tests include cwd-shaped high-entropy values, this needs a regression test or an explicit decision.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs\\\" start=154 priority=2 confidence=0.72}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P3] Growing transcript test misses append contract\\\" body=\\\"This test only asserts records_new. It would still pass if the new record was counted but not appended to the transcript list, or if duplicate envelopes were appended. Assert transcript_records_appended and final list length/hash to pin the intended behavior.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs\\\" start=1006 end=1018 priority=3 confidence=0.86}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P3] Session-key coverage is helper-shaped\\\" body=\\\"The session-key tests validate private helper formatting, but there is no capture-level regression for missing or unsafe session IDs remaining idempotent in GitMeta. That leaves the session dedupe behavior underprotected if wiring changes around GitMetaCaptureInput.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/capture.rs\\\" start=140 end=160 priority=3 confidence=0.68}\\n\\nCurrent tests look broadly balanced: the playbook’s core cases are mostly represented, especially malformed JSONL handling, cwd mismatch, dry-run no-write behavior, repeated capture, transcript hash-set loss, and broad redaction examples. The main gaps are around recovery/append intent and a few places where helper-level assertions do not fully prove the user-visible capture behavior.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-07T20:08:45.594Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user","content":[{"type":"input_text","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"::code-comment{title=\\\"[P2] Missing partial-write recovery coverage\\\" body=\\\"Tests cover missing transcript hash-set state when the transcript list still exists, but not the partial-write case where metadata hashes were recorded and transcript envelopes were not. A regression that derives transcript appends from metadata-new records would still pass.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs\\\" start=78 end=93 priority=2 confidence=0.78}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P2] Copied cwd redaction is untested\\\" body=\\\"Redaction integration tests cover copied session/message fields, but cwd is copied into the envelope without the same redaction path. Given the generic redaction tests include cwd-shaped high-entropy values, this needs a regression test or an explicit decision.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs\\\" start=154 priority=2 confidence=0.72}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P3] Growing transcript test misses append contract\\\" body=\\\"This test only asserts records_new. It would still pass if the new record was counted but not appended to the transcript list, or if duplicate envelopes were appended. Assert transcript_records_appended and final list length/hash to pin the intended behavior.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs\\\" start=1006 end=1018 priority=3 confidence=0.86}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P3] Session-key coverage is helper-shaped\\\" body=\\\"The session-key tests validate private helper formatting, but there is no capture-level regression for missing or unsafe session IDs remaining idempotent in GitMeta. That leaves the session dedupe behavior underprotected if wiring changes around GitMetaCaptureInput.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/capture.rs\\\" start=140 end=160 priority=3 confidence=0.68}\\n\\nCurrent tests look broadly balanced: the playbook’s core cases are mostly represented, especially malformed JSONL handling, cwd mismatch, dry-run no-write behavior, repeated capture, transcript hash-set loss, and broad redaction examples. The main gaps are around recovery/append intent and a few places where helper-level assertions do not fully prove the user-visible capture behavior.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>"}]}}}